15.63	The_Orphanage_(2007_film)	The Orphanage (2007 film)	The Orphanage (Spanish: ) is a 2007 Spanish horror film and the debut feature of Spanish filmmaker J.A. Bayona. The film stars Belén Rueda as Laura, Fernando Cayo as her husband, Carlos, and Roger Príncep as their adopted son Simón. The plot centers on Laura, who returns to her childhood home, an orphanage. Laura plans to turn the house into a home for disabled children, but a problem arises when she and Carlos realize that Simón believes he has a masked friend named Tomás with whom he will run away. After an argument with Laura, Simón is found to be missing.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2d/Elorfanato.jpg/220px-Elorfanato.jpg
